<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="29" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="29">
In describing 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Philippi" authorityYear="1860" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Eritrichium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eritrichium chaetocalyx" order="Boraginales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chaetocalyx">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Eritrichium chaetocalyx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.162865" author="Philippi, RA" journalOrPublisher="INTA, Buenos Aires" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" refId="B35" refString="Philippi, RA, 1860. Florula Atacamensis seu enumeratio plantarum, quas in itinere per desertum Atacamense. Sumptibus E. Anton. https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.162865" title="Florula Atacamensis seu enumeratio plantarum, quas in itinere per desertum Atacamense. Sumptibus E. Anton." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.162865" year="1860">Rudolph A. Philippi (1860)</bibRefCitation>
cited a gathering he made near Pan de 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Azúcar">Azucar</normalizedToken>
, Chile. Two duplicates of the type collection in agreement with the protologue and annotated by him as &quot; 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Philippi" authorityYear="1860" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Eritrichium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eritrichium chaetocalyx" order="Boraginales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chaetocalyx">Eritrichium chaetocalyx</taxonomicName>
&quot; were located at SGO. 
<bibRefCitation author="Johnston, IM" journalOrPublisher="Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" pagination="1 - 118" refId="B16" refString="Johnston, IM, 1927. Studies in the Boraginaceae VI. A revision of the South American Boraginoideae. Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University 78: 1 - 118" title="Studies in the Boraginaceae VI. A revision of the South American Boraginoideae." volume="78" year="1927">Johnston (1927)</bibRefCitation>
discussed this name and its original material, referring to a sheet lodged at SGO as the 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“type”">&quot;type&quot;</normalizedToken>
of the name. In this context, 
<bibRefCitation author="Johnston, IM" journalOrPublisher="Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" pagination="1 - 118" refId="B16" refString="Johnston, IM, 1927. Studies in the Boraginaceae VI. A revision of the South American Boraginoideae. Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University 78: 1 - 118" title="Studies in the Boraginaceae VI. A revision of the South American Boraginoideae." volume="78" year="1927">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Johnston’s">Johnston's</normalizedToken>
(1927)
</bibRefCitation>
statement must thus be considered as a first-step typification. Thus, in order to narrow this designation, the sheet SGO000004073 is here selected as a second-step lectotype.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="29">
In the protologue of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Philippi" authorityYear="1895" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Eritrichium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eritrichium divaricatum" order="Boraginales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="divaricatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Eritrichium divaricatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5354/0717-8883.2012.20872" author="Philippi, RA" journalOrPublisher="Anales de la Universidad de Chile" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" pagination="511 - 566" refId="B39" refString="Philippi, RA, 1895. Plantas nuevas chilenas de las familias que corresponden al tomo IV de la obra de Gay: (continuacion). Anales de la Universidad de Chile 90: 511 - 566, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5354/0717-8883.2012.20872" title="Plantas nuevas chilenas de las familias que corresponden al tomo IV de la obra de Gay: (continuacion)." url="https://doi.org/10.5354/0717-8883.2012.20872" volume="90" year="1895">Rudolph A. Philippi (1895)</bibRefCitation>
cited as type material a collection made by F. Philippi in Caldera, Chile. 
<bibRefCitation author="Johnston, IM" journalOrPublisher="Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" pagination="1 - 118" refId="B16" refString="Johnston, IM, 1927. Studies in the Boraginaceae VI. A revision of the South American Boraginoideae. Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University 78: 1 - 118" title="Studies in the Boraginaceae VI. A revision of the South American Boraginoideae." volume="78" year="1927">Johnston (1927)</bibRefCitation>
referred to a specimen kept at SGO as the 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“type”">&quot;type&quot;</normalizedToken>
of the name, although two sheets annotated, in R. A. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Philippi’s">Philippi's</normalizedToken>
hand, as &quot; 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Philippi" authorityYear="1895" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Eritrichium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eritrichium divaricatum" order="Boraginales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="divaricatum">Eritrichium divaricatum</taxonomicName>
&quot; are found there. This situation determines that 
<bibRefCitation author="Johnston, IM" journalOrPublisher="Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" pagination="1 - 118" refId="B16" refString="Johnston, IM, 1927. Studies in the Boraginaceae VI. A revision of the South American Boraginoideae. Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University 78: 1 - 118" title="Studies in the Boraginaceae VI. A revision of the South American Boraginoideae." volume="78" year="1927">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Johnston’s">Johnston's</normalizedToken>
(1927)
</bibRefCitation>
statement must be considered as a first-step lectotypification. In this context, the duplicate SGO000004070 is here selected as a second-step lectotype (Art. 9.17 of the ICN; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.12705/Code.2018" author="Turland, NJ" journalOrPublisher="Annals of the Missouri Botanical Garden" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" refId="B51" refString="Turland, NJ, Wiersema, JH, Barrie, FR, Greuter, W, Hawksworth, DL, Herendeen, PS, Knapp, S, Kusber, WH, Li, DZ, Marhold, K, May, TW, McNeill, J, Monro, AM, Prad, J, Price, MJ, Smith, GF, 2018. International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Vegetabile 159. Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashuetten. https://doi.org/10.12705/Code.2018" title="International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Vegetabile 159. Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashuetten." url="https://doi.org/10.12705/Code.2018" year="2018">Turland et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="29">
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5354/0717-8883.2012.20872" author="Philippi, RA" journalOrPublisher="Anales de la Universidad de Chile" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" pagination="511 - 566" refId="B39" refString="Philippi, RA, 1895. Plantas nuevas chilenas de las familias que corresponden al tomo IV de la obra de Gay: (continuacion). Anales de la Universidad de Chile 90: 511 - 566, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5354/0717-8883.2012.20872" title="Plantas nuevas chilenas de las familias que corresponden al tomo IV de la obra de Gay: (continuacion)." url="https://doi.org/10.5354/0717-8883.2012.20872" volume="90" year="1895">Rudolph A. Philippi (1895)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Eritrichium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eritrichium pustulosum" order="Boraginales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pustulosum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Eritrichium pustulosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on a specimen he collected in Caldera, Chile. According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Johnston, IM" journalOrPublisher="Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" pagination="1 - 118" refId="B16" refString="Johnston, IM, 1927. Studies in the Boraginaceae VI. A revision of the South American Boraginoideae. Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University 78: 1 - 118" title="Studies in the Boraginaceae VI. A revision of the South American Boraginoideae." volume="78" year="1927">Johnston (1927)</bibRefCitation>
, the type material of the name is lodged at SGO. However, three sheets linked to 
<taxonomicName genus="E." lsidName="E. pustulosum" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" rank="species" species="pustulosum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">E. pustulosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, in agreement with the protologue, were located at SGO, which can certainly be considered as original material. In this context, 
<bibRefCitation author="Johnston, IM" journalOrPublisher="Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" pagination="1 - 118" refId="B16" refString="Johnston, IM, 1927. Studies in the Boraginaceae VI. A revision of the South American Boraginoideae. Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University 78: 1 - 118" title="Studies in the Boraginaceae VI. A revision of the South American Boraginoideae." volume="78" year="1927">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Johnston’s">Johnston's</normalizedToken>
(1927)
</bibRefCitation>
statement must be considered as a first-step lectotypification. In order to narrow this earlier designation, the sheet SGO000004125 is here selected as a second-step lectotype.
</paragraph>
